The paper deals with the design of an observer for a class of nonlinear systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of Active Disturbance Rejection Control (ADRC) and output feedback techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of control engineering (cs.CE). The application of the proposed observer to a Permanent Magnet DC (PMDC) motor indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of nonlinear functions and finite-time Lyapunov principles suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
